Title: Retinal detachment caused by disinsertion of the ora serrata. Study of 100 cases treated by various methods.
Abstract: A presentation of 100 cases of retinal detachment caused by retinal disinsertion reviewed over 25 years. The overall sucess rate (84 per cent) improves to 95 per cent with the introduction of cryotherapy associated with Lincoff sponges.
