Title: A case of supravalvular aortic stenosis treated by Doty's operation.
Abstract: A 11-year-old boy with supravalvular aortic stenosis was treated by extended aortoplasty (Doty's operation) with excellent results. The extended aortoplasty provided satisfactory relief of aortic stenosis and improved function of the aortic valve.
