Title: Six cases of severe head injury treated by exercise in addition to other therapies.
Abstract: Six cases of severe head injury treated with vigorous early morning exercise in addition to more orthodox therapies are presented. Observations on behaviour and psychometric testing have been used to assess results. Discussion is centred round the benefits of early morning exercise.
