Abstract: A case of sideroblastic anemia arised in multiple myeloma is related. Eighteen cases of literature are studied. This evolution usually appears in old and remitted myeloma. The pathogeny of the sideroblastic anemia is unknown, and possibly related to leukemia complicating multiple myeloma.
