Title: A case of Lennox-Gastaut syndrome successfully treated by removal of a parietotemporal astrocytoma.
Abstract: We report a case of Lennox-Gastaut-type epilepsy that was followed for 3 years. The patient showed typical EEG findings and later a parietotemporal astrocytoma (type II) on the left. Removal of the tumor was followed by recovery of the child and disappearance of EEG epileptic elements.
