Title: 5 kg sternal chondroma, treated by resection and silastic prosthesis. Satisfactory result.
Abstract: Resection of the sternum and adjacent, cartilages raises difficult problems of reconstruction. The tumour, which, exceeding 5 kg was considered histologically as a chondroma, was replaced by a silastic prosthesis with an excellent result 13 months later.
