Title: Active tuberculous coxarthritis in the adult. 2 cases treated by total arthroplasty with a follow-up of 7 and 3 years.
Abstract: Cemented total hip replacements were performed on two patients with active tuberculous arthritis. Chemotherapy was administrated for 3 months pre-operatively and continued for 15 months. Excellent results were observed after 3 and 7 years, respectively.
