Title: A long surviving hepatocellular carcinoma case (2 years 1 month) with tumor thrombus in the portal trunk treated by embolization.
Abstract: A 55-year-old male patient suffered from hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) with tumor thrombus in the portal trunk and cavernous transformation in the liver hilus. He was treated 4 times effectively by transcatheter arterial embolization (TAE). Tumor thrombus in the portal trunk which was demonstrated by portography before TAE disappeared following initial TAE. He is still alive 2 years and 1 month after initial TAE. We reported a long surviving case with advanced HCC treated by TAE and TAE for advanced HCC was discussed.
